# Mattermost implementation patterns

Read this skill before writing code. Match surrounding files in the area you touch.

## Repo map

| Area | Path | Role |
|------|------|------|
| HTTP API | `server/channels/api4/` | Routes, permission checks, JSON, audit |
| Business logic | `server/channels/app/` | Rules, plugins, websockets, orchestration |
| Persistence | `server/channels/store/` + `store/sqlstore/` | Interfaces + SQL |
| Models / API types | `server/public/model/` | Shared structs, permissions, errors |
| Web UI | `webapp/channels/src/components/` | React |
| Redux | `webapp/channels/src/actions/`, `webapp/platform/mattermost-redux/` | Thunks, entity state |
| HTTP client | `webapp/platform/client/` | `Client4` |
| OpenAPI | `api/v4/source/` | Public API reference |
| Migrations | `server/channels/db/migrations/postgres/` | Schema changes |
| Plugins | `server/public/plugin/` | Hook RPC, plugin API |

Always load area-specific rules:

- `@AGENTS.md` (root PR + Cloud Agent notes)
- `@server/AGENTS.md` (Go modules, i18n)
- `@webapp/AGENTS.md` (shared components)
- `@server/channels/README.md` (SQL/API performance)
- `@server/channels/db/migrations/README.md` (migration safety)

For layer-by-layer templates and examples, see [reference.md](reference.md).

## Implementation workflow

1. **Find the vertical slice** — Search for the closest existing feature (same entity or route family). Copy its file layout and naming.
2. **Work bottom-up or top-down consistently** — Typical order for a new REST feature:
   - `model` (if new types/permissions)
   - `store` interface + `sqlstore` implementation
   - `app` method(s)
   - `api4` handler + `Init*` registration
   - `Client4` method
   - Redux action + reducer/selector if UI needs it
   - Component
   - `api/v4/source/*.yaml` if the route is public API
3. **Permissions first** — Enforce in `api4` (and mirror checks in `app` when reused from jobs/plugins). Use `SessionHasPermissionTo*` / `SetPermissionError`; do not skip checks.
4. **Keep layers thin** — `api4`: decode, audit, permission, call `App`, encode. `app`: business rules, hooks, side effects. `store`: SQL only.
5. **Tests at the layer you changed** — `api4/*_test.go`, `app/*_test.go`, `store/storetest/`, or RTL component tests. Run targeted tests before widening scope.

## Server: new REST endpoint (checklist)

- [ ] Add route in `func (api *API) InitFoo()` using `api.BaseRoutes.*` and the right wrapper:
  - `APISessionRequired` — logged-in user (most routes)
  - `APIHandler` — no session
  - `APISessionRequiredMfa`, `APISessionRequiredDisableWhenBusy`, `RemoteClusterTokenRequired` — only when matching neighbors
- [ ] Handler signature: `func name(c *Context, w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`
- [ ] Decode with `json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode`; invalid input → `c.SetInvalidParam` / `SetInvalidParamWithErr`
- [ ] Set `auditRec` for mutating operations (`c.MakeAuditRecord`, `defer c.LogAuditRecWithLevel`)
- [ ] Call `c.App.*(c.AppContext, ...)`; on error set `c.Err` and return
- [ ] Respond with `json.NewEncoder(w).Encode` and appropriate `w.WriteHeader`
- [ ] Register `InitFoo()` from the API init chain (grep an existing `InitPost`-style call)
- [ ] Add `api4` test using `TestMainHelper` / `th := Setup(t)` patterns from sibling `*_test.go`

## Server: app + store

- [ ] Add store method on the `*Store` interface in `server/channels/store/store.go`
- [ ] Implement in `server/channels/store/sqlstore/*_store.go` (`Sql*Store`, `request.CTX` on mutating methods)
- [ ] Add `storetest` coverage when behavior is non-trivial
- [ ] App method returns `*model.AppError` for user-facing failures; use `model.NewAppError` with an i18n id
- [ ] After `i18n/en.json` edits: `make i18n-extract` (from `server/`)
- [ ] Never run `go mod tidy`; use `make modules-tidy`

## Database migrations

Follow `server/channels/db/migrations/README.md` strictly.

- [ ] One concern per migration; next sequence in `db/migrations/postgres/`
- [ ] Files: `{seq}_{description}.up.sql` and `.down.sql`
- [ ] Run `make migrations-extract` after adding files
- [ ] No full-table locks: use `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY`, phased column adds, batch jobs — not monolithic `UPDATE`
- [ ] Do not edit shipped migrations; add a new one to fix mistakes
- [ ] Release note required for schema changes (see PR template)

## Webapp: UI + data

Follow `webapp/STYLE_GUIDE.md` and `webapp/AGENTS.md`.

- [ ] Functional components; `useSelector` / `useDispatch` (not new `connect`)
- [ ] `@mattermost/shared` for `Button`, `WithTooltip`; `@mattermost/components` for `GenericModal`
- [ ] Co-located `ComponentName.scss`, BEM root `.ComponentName`
- [ ] All user-visible strings via `FormattedMessage` / `useIntl` (not `localizeMessage`)
- [ ] New API surface: method on `Client4` in `webapp/platform/client`
- [ ] Redux thunk returns `{data}` or `{error}`; prefer `bindClientFunc` for Client4 calls
- [ ] Server-backed state in `mattermost-redux` / `state.entities`; UI-only persisted state in `state.views`
- [ ] Tests: RTL via `utils/react_testing_utils`, `renderWithContext`, `userEvent`, no snapshots

## Plugins and hooks

- [ ] Server hooks: implement on plugin struct in `server/public/plugin/hooks.go`; business flow calls hooks from `app` (e.g. `MessageWillBePosted`)
- [ ] Do not duplicate permission logic inside plugins; enforce before hooks when possible
- [ ] Webapp plugin hooks: see `webapp/channels/src/actions/hooks.ts` for client-side hook runners

## API documentation

When adding or changing a public REST route:

- [ ] Update the appropriate file under `api/v4/source/` (e.g. `channels.yaml`, `posts.yaml`)
- [ ] Add definitions to `api/v4/source/definitions.yaml` when needed
- [ ] Verify with `make build` in `api/`

## Pull requests

Follow `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`: remove HTML comments, omit empty sections, always include the `release-note` block (`NONE` if no user/API/schema impact).

## Anti-patterns

- Business logic or SQL in `api4` handlers
- Direct `Client4` usage in React components (use actions)
- `go mod tidy` instead of `make modules-tidy`
- New migrations that rewrite large tables in one transaction
- Hand-rolled buttons/tooltips/modals when shared components exist
- Copy-pasting permission checks from one-off “temporary” api4 patterns unless intentionally matching that legacy path
